AZURE WORKSHOP |DAY-2 |SESSION-2

HOW TO CREATE A VIRTUAL MACHINE IN WINDOWS AND CONNECT TO RDP FILE:

1)Login to you Azure Account.
2)Click on "+Create resource" or search for "Virtual Machine".
3)Then click on Virtual machine to create.
4)Enter the following detail:
    -> Subscription : default
    -> resource group : [your choice]
    -> virtual machine name:[your choice]
    -> Region : default
    -> Image : Windows 2022 Datacenter -x64
3)Administrator account
      -> create a username
      -> create a password
4)In inbound ports choose allow selected ports.
5)And check for (RDP 3389)
6) And just go for "review + create"
7) Click create to create your virtual machine.

8)After deployed your virtual machine click on "connect"
9)download your RDP file.
10)Install the RDP file and allow the access shown.
11)Finally you connected you virtual machine to RDP File.
